**Answer:** The WMS is a firm-level panel covering 10,282 manufacturing firms across 24 countries, observed in up to 11 waves between 2004 and 2015 (14,277 observations total). The panel is highly **unbalanced**: 7,088 firms (69%) appear only once, another 2,510 appear twice. Only the 3,194 firms observed two or more times contribute to the fixed effects estimates — the effective FE sample is roughly 5,900 observations, about 41% of the raw total.

---

